The problem is that your document requirements exceeds the accuracy of a 
single precision float. It is not required that an SVG user agent store 
all values as double precision however they should be manipulated in double 
precision.  We do conform to this.

It would be nice if Batik handled this document but the document is in fact
outside the conformance requiements of the SVG specification at least as I read
them, see section 4.1 Basic Datatypes:

    Unless stated otherwise for a particular attribute or property, a 
    <number> has the capacity for at least a singleprecision floating point
    number (see [ICC32]) and has a range (at a minimum) of -3.4e+38F to 
    +3.4e+38F.

    It is recommended that higher precision floating point storage and 
    computation be performed on operations such as coordinate system 
    transformations to provide the best possible precision and to prevent 
    round-off errors.

    Conforming High-Quality SVG Viewers are required to use at least 
    double-precision floating point (see [ICC32]) for intermediate 
    calculations on certain numerical operations.
